{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cdbf4fff-ef46-4772-a797-94bc16d3d43d","content":"Since you already have the dump file, you're past the collection phase. Here's how to analyze it:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM issues) |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch threads |\n\n**Using LLDB** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-sos\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) to see the crash reason, then `clrstack` for the stack trace. Would you like help running any of these?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e1fd8bcb-826b-4d73-8526-336be9abf237","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"7854:588E9:1F1FA6A:22AF079:69FA9F2B"},"id":"c17c9847-93f7-417a-a525-eb57577df9bd","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:53:59.649Z","parentId":"0035ff69-6839-4bcd-87ea-4ccef980792c"}
